    • Method Detail

      • getNextJosmVersion

        public static org.gradle.api.artifacts.Dependency getNextJosmVersion(org.gradle.api.Project $receiver,
                                                                     java.lang.String startVersion)

        Finds the next JOSM version available in the repositories known to Gradle, starting with a given version number.

        If the number can be parsed as an integer, 50 version numbers beginning with the given number are checked. Otherwise only the given version is checked.

        Returns:
        the next available JOSM dependency. A DependencySet consisting only of this one dependency.
        Throws:
        - if no suitable JOSM version can be found.

      • getAllRequiredJosmPlugins

        public static java.util.Set<org.gradle.api.artifacts.Dependency> getAllRequiredJosmPlugins(org.gradle.api.Project $receiver,
                                                                                           java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> directlyRequiredPlugins)

        Resolves the JOSM plugin names given as parameter, using the available repositories for this project. Not only are the given plugin names resolved to Dependencies, but also all JOSM plugins on which these plugins depend.

        The resolution is aborted, if a dependency chain exceeds 10 plugins (plugin 1 depends on plugin 2 â€¦ depends on plugin 10). This limit can be changed by JosmPluginExtension.maxPluginDependencyDepth

        Parameters:
        directlyRequiredPlugins - a Set of Strings representing the names of JOSM plugins. These plugins (and their dependencies) will be resolved
        Returns:
        a set of Dependency objects, including the requested plugins, plus all plugins required by the requested plugins
